.TH "meson_sm_call_read" 9 "meson_sm_call_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
meson_sm_call_read \- retrieve data from secure-monitor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" meson_sm_call_read
.BI "(struct meson_sm_firmware *fw "  ","
.BI "void *buffer "  ","
.BI "unsigned int bsize "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd_index "  ","
.BI "u32 arg0 "  ","
.BI "u32 arg1 "  ","
.BI "u32 arg2 "  ","
.BI "u32 arg3 "  ","
.BI "u32 arg4 "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fw" 12
Pointer to secure-monitor firmware
.IP "buffer" 12
Buffer to store the retrieved data
.IP "bsize" 12
Size of the buffer
.IP "cmd_index" 12
Index of the SMC32 function ID
.IP "arg0" 12
SMC32 Argument 0
.IP "arg1" 12
SMC32 Argument 1
.IP "arg2" 12
SMC32 Argument 2
.IP "arg3" 12
SMC32 Argument 3
.IP "arg4" 12
SMC32 Argument 4
.SH "RETURN"
size of read data on success, a negative value on error
When 0 is returned there is no guarantee about the amount of
data read and bsize bytes are copied in buffer.
